    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-09-04T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-09-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="69"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.00/8–2946: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Saigon</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-09-04T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 4, 1946—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>240. Action <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 354 Aug 26<note n="58"
                        xml:id="d69fn1">Not printed.</note> commended. Lose no opportunity
                    counteract with persons responsible press orientation, and in manner you deem
                    most effective, French colonial tendency picture US as aggressive and
                    imperialistic. This brings certain French colonials, unwittingly for most part,
                    very close to Communist Party line.</p>
                <p>With his knowledge US Clarac (reurtel 357 Aug 29<note n="58" xml:id="d69fn2">Not
                        printed.</note>) should know better than encourage anti-American suspicions
                    this juncture Franco-American relations, and <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> believes he can be persuaded take and foster attitude required
                    by logic events.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clayton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
